= Andrew Stitt =

**Homepage:** none right now, check back later

**IRC nick(s):** afrayedknot

**Role in SMGL:** At present I'm just some random guy on IRC. Past roles have been section maintainer and grimoire wizard. I wrote a spell test framework called "Prometheus" and was sorcery team lead for a while.

**Age/Birthdate:** 25

**Location/Country:** San Francisco, California

== Common ==

**When did you first start using Linux and why?**

I tried linux out a few times, first starting around 1998. In 2001 I decided to ditch my tired windows 95 install for good. I switched because I wanted to be more in touch with how my computer was operating, I felt that proprietary offerings were too unstable and opaque. I also wanted to get involved in an open source project and become more familiar with how computers operate. Or something.

**How long have you been using the [[About|SMGL]] distribution?**

Since 2002.. and stuff.

**What piqued your interest in SMGL initially?**

I wanted a source based distribution that mirrored upstream defaults, one that was ideally an automated version of Linux From Scratch.

**Tell us a little bit about yourself. Education/Career/Skills?**

I work as a software engineer in the San Francisco Bay Area. I graduated from UC Santa Cruz in 2003 with a degree in Computer Science. \\ http://www.linkedin.com/pub/1/5a4/718

**Any personal messages for the Source Mage users out there?**

The most important thing is to have fun with it.

**What other OS programs/software have you worked on?**

Mostly work stuff. I worked on a storage cluster at one job, then on navigation software, presently I work under NDA.

== Flamewars ==

**vi or emacs?**

I usually use vim, sometimes I use nano, but only when there isn't vim or vim is configured in such a way that I cannot use it.

**KDE or GNOME?**

I don't really care so long as I can get to a bash prompt. If I have a choice I usually setup pwm.

**BSD or GPL?**

GPL for all of my code at least. But I don't have an issue with BSD.

